ej,goslg101,P,evanb901,Intentionally spiking pitcher Bert Cole $Cole's first pitch sailed near Goslin's head. Goslin walked towards Cole with his club raised; Ump Connolly grabbed him by the arm and led him back to the batter's box.  After knocking four pop fouls, he grounded to Burns with Cole covering 1B. As Goslin neared the bag, he jumped on Cole and knocked him over.  When Cole got up and rushed Goslin, Ump Evans got between them.  Players of both teams surrounded them.  As Goslin returned to the bench he was greeted with a shower of pop bottles.  A sack of peanuts struck him in the face. Police went over to the LF stands to quiet the crowd. Coles pant legs were badly ripped.1925CLE.EVA.regular.comment.csv"
